### 2. Car data input and storage

| Short name | User story title | User story description | Priority | Acceptance criteria |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| DATA-01 | Upload vehicle history | As a user, I want to be able to upload data about my car (repairs, mileage, technical condition, trips, refueling) so that I can conveniently store the entire history in a single digital space (car timeline). | Must |   • The user can add a repair record with: date, mileage, description, cost, replaced parts, photo (optional)
  • The user can add a refueling record with: date, mileage, liters, cost, fuel type
  • The user can add a trip record with: date, start mileage, end mileage, route (optional)
  • All records are automatically linked to the selected car.Records are displayed in chronological order
  • The user can edit and delete any record
  • After adding, editing, or deleting a record, the record list updates automatically (no manual refresh required)
  • The system does not allow entering a mileage value lower than any previously recorded mileage for that car |
| DATA-02 | Update parts and condition | As a user, I want to upload data about newly installed parts or select them from a catalog so that I can keep up-to-date information about the car’s condition. | Should |   • The user can add a part with: part name, installation date, mileage at installation, lifespan (km), photo (optional)
  • The user can select a part from a predefined catalog (e.g., oil, filter, timing belt, brake pads)
  • When selected from the catalog, the system may auto-fill a typical lifespan if known
  • The user can manually edit the part's lifespan
  • The user can mark a part as **replaced**
  • When this happens:the current part record is preserved with a "replaced" flag;a new part record is created (with new date and mileage) OR the user is guided to the "add part" flow. |
| DATA-03 | Car photo/3D model | As a user, I want to upload photos of my car so that I can see its 3D model (or photo) in the car profile. | Could |   • The user can upload one or more car photos
  • The uploaded photo is saved and displayed on the car card in the Garage
  • The user can delete or replace a photo
  • Supported formats: JPG, PNG 
  • If multiple photos are uploaded, a swipeable gallery is available
  • If the user uploads enough photos, the system may suggest generating a simplified 3D model |

